{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771247940,"nonce":"drciuTAb1cD7+nw3oq8+C4po1NQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rTdQT","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/210","origin":"github"},"title":"fix: status_report.sh shows false-positive flags for all repos due to path and branch parsing bugs","message":"## Bug\n\n`status_report.sh` shows false-positive \"🔀 Non-Jazzy?\" and \"❓ Untracked\" flags for **all 21 project repos**, even though every repo is clean and on the correct branch.\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThree interrelated bugs in the repo status parsing logic:\n\n1. **Path prefix mismatch** (line 249): `vcs custom` outputs repo paths like `./src/marine_ais`, but `get_repo_info.py` and `list_overlay_repos.py --format names` expect just `marine_ais`. The `sed` extraction preserves the `./src/` prefix, causing all lookups to fail.\n\n2. **Branch extraction includes tracking info** (line 264): `awk '{print $1}'` extracts `jazzy...origin/jazzy` (no spaces to split on) instead of just `jazzy`, so branch comparisons always fail.\n\n3. **Hard-coded \"jazzy\" fallback** (line 224): When `get_repo_info.py` returns \"unknown\" (due to bug #1), the script falls back to comparing against a hard-coded `\"jazzy\"` string instead of using the configured expected branch from `.repos` files.\n\n### Fix\n\n- Strip path prefix from `current_repo` to just the basename\n- Split branch on `...` to extract only the local branch name\n- Remove the hard-coded \"jazzy\" fallback — with the path fix, `get_repo_info.py` will correctly resolve configured repos\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}